---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Aetna International in Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-aetna', text: 'Why Aetna for Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'us-connection', text: 'US Connection Benefits', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Panama', href: '/countries/panama/insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs Cigna', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 55)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Pioneer', coverage: 'Core coverage', price: '$260-340/mo' },
  { plan: 'Navigator', coverage: 'Enhanced', price: '$340-440/mo' },
  { plan: 'Voyager', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$420-540/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International Health Insurance in Panama"
  description="Guide to Aetna International health insurance for expats in Panama. US-backed coverage with strong Americas network."
  headline="Aetna International in Panama"
  subheadline="CVS Health-backed international coverage. Strong option for American expats maintaining US healthcare connections."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/panama-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Aetna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Aetna International in Panama</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International, backed by CVS Health, offers international health insurance with strong US connections. For American expats in Panama who want seamless coverage between Panama and the US, Aetna provides integrated solutions.
  </p>
  <p>
    With a well-known brand and established Americas network, Aetna appeals particularly to US retirees and corporate expats familiar with the company.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$280-450</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 55)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">CVS Health</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Parent company</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Americas</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Network strength</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Aetna Panama Quote"
    description="US-backed coverage for Panama expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-aetna">Why Aetna for Panama</h2>

  <h3>US Healthcare Integration</h3>
  <p>
    For American expats, Aetna's US roots provide advantages:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Familiar brand and processes</li>
    <li>Strong US provider network when visiting home</li>
    <li>Integrated prescription drug coverage via CVS</li>
    <li>Seamless claims between US and Panama</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Americas Network</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna has built strong networks throughout the Americas, including Panama:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Relationships with Panama's major private hospitals</li>
    <li>Direct billing arrangements</li>
    <li>Regional coordination for medical evacuations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Corporate Continuity</h3>
  <p>
    If you had Aetna coverage through a US employer, transitioning to Aetna International provides continuity and familiarity.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">CVS Prescription Benefits</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Aetna's CVS Health backing provides advantages for prescription medications. Members can often use CVS pharmacies when in the US and access competitive prescription pricing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 55-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, and coverage selections.
  </p>

  <h3>Plan Comparison</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pioneer:</strong> Core inpatient, emergency, evacuation coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Navigator:</strong> Adds outpatient care, specialists, expanded benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Voyager:</strong> Comprehensive coverage including wellness and enhanced mental health</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deductible Options</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>$0 - Highest premium, no out-of-pocket for covered services</li>
    <li>$1,000-$2,500 - Moderate savings</li>
    <li>$5,000+ - Significant premium reduction</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU, rehabilitation</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics (Navigator+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
    <li><strong>Prescriptions:</strong> Comprehensive drug coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Better than average coverage (Voyager)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Notable Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>24/7 member services</li>
    <li>Telemedicine services</li>
    <li>Health and wellness programs</li>
    <li>Second opinion services</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Medical underwriting required</li>
    <li>Dental/vision: Separate add-ons with limited benefits</li>
    <li>Alternative medicine: Limited or excluded</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="us-connection">US Connection Benefits</h2>

  <h3>For American Retirees</h3>
  <p>
    Many Panama retirees maintain ties to the US. Aetna's integration helps:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Family visits:</strong> Full coverage when visiting the US</li>
    <li><strong>Specialized care:</strong> Access US facilities for complex cases</li>
    <li><strong>Prescriptions:</strong> Fill prescriptions at US pharmacies</li>
    <li><strong>Familiar processes:</strong> US-style customer service and claims</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medicare Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    US Medicare doesn't cover care in Panama. Aetna International can fill this gap:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Primary coverage in Panama</li>
    <li>US coverage when visiting (may coordinate with Medicare if maintained)</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation to US facilities if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Age-Related Pricing</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age 55:</strong> $280-450/month</li>
    <li><strong>Age 65:</strong> $420-650/month</li>
    <li><strong>Age 75:</strong> $600-900/month</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Pre-existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna uses medical underwriting. Options include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full disclosure with individual assessment</li>
    <li>Some conditions covered, others excluded</li>
    <li>Moratorium options may be available</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Aetna Plans for Panama"
    description="US-integrated coverage for American expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage are estimates. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your specific needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
